pivot_genre_frequency = genre_frequency.pivot(index='Aired', columns='Genre', values='Frequency').fillna(0)

genres_to_drop = ['Hentai', 'UNKNOWN', 'Girls Love', 'Boys Love', 'Ecchi', 'Erotica', 'Award Winning', 'Slice of Life'] # Getting rid of the niche ones just so the graph is actually readable
filtered_genre_frequency = pivot_genre_frequency.drop(columns=genres_to_drop, errors='ignore')

# merge some genres
filtered_genre_frequency['Fantasy / Sci-Fi'] = filtered_genre_frequency[['Fantasy', 'Sci-Fi']].sum(axis=1)
filtered_genre_frequency['Other'] = filtered_genre_frequency[['Avant Garde', 'Gourmet']].sum(axis=1)
filtered_genre_frequency['Mystery '] = filtered_genre_frequency[['Mystery', 'Suspense']].sum(axis=1)
filtered_genre_frequency['Supernatural '] = filtered_genre_frequency[['Supernatural', 'Horror']].sum(axis=1)

# dropping stuff that I merged or won't use
filtered_genre_frequency.drop(columns=['Fantasy', 'Sci-Fi'], inplace=True)
filtered_genre_frequency.drop(columns=['Avant Garde', 'Gourmet'], inplace=True)
filtered_genre_frequency.drop(columns=['Mystery', 'Suspense'], inplace=True)

import ast
traits_by_year = []

for year in years:

  most_common_traits_year_over_year = anime_traits[anime_traits['Released'].isin([year])]
  males = most_common_traits_year_over_year[most_common_traits_year_over_year['Gender'].isin(['Male'])]
  females = most_common_traits_year_over_year[most_common_traits_year_over_year['Gender'].isin(['Female'])]
  trait_dic_male = {}
  trait_dic_female = {}

  for i, male in males.iterrows():
    tags = ast.literal_eval(male['Tags'])
    for tag in tags:
      if tag in trait_dic_male:
        trait_dic_male[tag] += 1
      else:
        trait_dic_male[tag] = 1

  for i, female in females.iterrows():
    tags = ast.literal_eval(female['Tags'])
    for tag in tags:
      if tag in trait_dic_female:
        trait_dic_female[tag] += 1
      else:
        trait_dic_female[tag] = 1

  trait_dic_male_sorted = sorted(trait_dic_male.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
  trait_dic_female_sorted = sorted(trait_dic_female.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
  trait_dic_male_sorted = trait_dic_male_sorted[:30]
  trait_dic_female_sorted = trait_dic_female_sorted[:30]

  traits_by_year.append({'Year': year, 'Male Traits': trait_dic_male_sorted,
                         'Female Traits': trait_dic_female_sorted})

traits_by_year_df = pd.DataFrame(traits_by_year)

# Ratio of teenagers to adults year over year
teens_to_adults = []

for i, traits_in_year in traits_by_year_df.iterrows():
  male_traits = traits_in_year['Male Traits']
  male_adult = 0
  male_teenager = 0

  for trait, count in male_traits:
      if trait == 'Adult':
          male_adult = count
      elif trait == 'Teenager':
          male_teenager = count

  female_traits = traits_in_year['Female Traits']
  female_adult = 0
  female_teenager = 0

  for trait, count in female_traits:
      if trait == 'Adult':
          female_adult = count
      elif trait == 'Teenager':
          female_teenager = count

  total_guys = male_adult + male_teenager
  total_girls = female_adult + female_teenager
  guys_to_girls_ratio = 0
  if total_guys != 0 and total_girls != 0:
    guys_to_girls_ratio = total_guys / (total_guys + total_girls)

  teens_to_adults.append({'Year': traits_in_year['Year'], 'Male Adults': male_adult,
                         'Male Teeangers': male_teenager,
                          'Total Guys' : total_guys,
                          'Female Adults': female_adult,
                         'Female Teeangers': female_teenager,
                          'Total Girls' : total_girls,
                          'Guys to Girls Ratio' : guys_to_girls_ratio
                          })

teens_to_adults_df = pd.DataFrame(teens_to_adults)

import ast
import pandas as pd

traits_by_year_ignoring_age = []

# So I also modified this a bit so its using just '1998' instead of the YMD format :] (also for some reason the revision history doesn't show that I modified this cell? lol)

for year in years:
    most_common_traits_year_over_year = anime_traits[anime_traits['Released'].isin([year])]

    males = most_common_traits_year_over_year[most_common_traits_year_over_year['Gender'].isin(['Male'])]
    females = most_common_traits_year_over_year[most_common_traits_year_over_year['Gender'].isin(['Female'])]

    trait_dics = {'Male Adult': {}, 'Male Teenager': {}, 'Male Child': {}, 'Female Adult': {}, 'Female Teenager': {}, 'Female Child': {}}

    for gender in [males, females]:
        for i, row in gender.iterrows():
            tags = ast.literal_eval(row['Tags'])
            age_group = 'Adult'
            if 'Adult' in tags:
                age_group = 'Adult'
            elif 'Teenager' in tags:
                age_group = 'Teenager'
            elif 'Child' in tags:
                age_group = 'Child'

            for tag in tags:
                if tag != age_group:
                    if tag in trait_dics[f'{row["Gender"]} {age_group}']:
                        trait_dics[f'{row["Gender"]} {age_group}'][tag] += 1
                    else:
                        trait_dics[f'{row["Gender"]} {age_group}'][tag] = 1

    for gender in trait_dics:
        trait_dics[gender] = sorted(trait_dics[gender].items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)
        trait_dics[gender] = trait_dics[gender][:20]

    traits_by_year_ignoring_age.append({
        'Year': year.year,  # Extracting just the year component
        'Male Adult Traits': trait_dics['Male Adult'],
        'Male Teenager Traits': trait_dics['Male Teenager'],
        'Male Child Traits': trait_dics['Male Child'],
        'Female Adult Traits': trait_dics['Female Adult'],
        'Female Teenager Traits': trait_dics['Female Teenager'],
        'Female Child Traits': trait_dics['Female Child'],
    })

traits_by_year_ignoring_age_df = pd.DataFrame(traits_by_year_ignoring_age)
